verblex: 1. To have consumed enough food or drink. English = (be) full.
2. To be as much as you need or want of something. English = (be) enough, (be) sufficient; suffice.
3. To be bored or annoyed. English = (be) fed up.
interj: 1. Used alone, especially with children, to mean you want your addressee to stop doing what they have been doing because it irritates you, is disruptive or is inappropriate behaviour. English = 'That's enough!'.
